  "dn2:77.0": "4.3.2.6. Second Absorption ",

# "ANCHOR-REMAP",
  "dn7:3.1": "They enter and remain in the second absorption … ",
  "dn2:77.1": "Furthermore, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and mind at one, without applying the mind and keeping it connected. ",

  "dn2:77.2": "They drench, steep, fill, and spread their body with rapture and bliss born of immersion. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with rapture and bliss born of immersion. ",

  "dn2:78.1": "It’s like a deep lake fed by spring water. There’s no inlet to the east, west, north, or south, and the heavens would not properly bestow showers from time to time. ",
  "dn2:78.2": "But the stream of cool water welling up in the lake drenches, steeps, fills, and spreads throughout the lake. There’s no part of the lake that’s not spread through with cool water. ",
  "dn2:78.3": "In the same way, a mendicant drenches, steeps, fills, and spreads their body with rapture and bliss born of immersion. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with rapture and bliss born of immersion. ",
  "dn7:2.5": "When a mendicant knows and sees like this, would it be appropriate to say of them: ",
  "dn7:2.6": "‘The soul and the body are the same thing’ or ‘The soul and the body are different things’?” ",
  "dn7:2.7": "“It would, reverend.” ",
  "dn7:2.8": "",
  "dn7:2.9": "“But reverends, I know and see like this. ",
  "dn7:2.10": "Nevertheless, I do not say: ",
  "dn7:2.11": "‘The soul and the body are the same thing’ or ‘The soul and the body are different things’. … ",

# "dn2:78.4  VIRTUAL-REMAP  2nd combined",

  "dn2:79.0": "4.3.2.7. Third Absorption ",

# "ANCHOR-REMAP",
  "dn7:3.2": "third absorption … ",
  "dn2:79.1": "Furthermore, with the fading away of rapture, a mendicant enters and remains in the third absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’ ",

  "dn2:79.2": "They drench, steep, fill, and spread their body with bliss free of rapture. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with bliss free of rapture. ",

  "dn2:80.1": "It’s like a pool with blue water lilies, or pink or white lotuses. Some of them sprout and grow in the water without rising above it, thriving underwater. From the tip to the root they’re drenched, steeped, filled, and soaked with cool water. There’s no part of them that’s not soaked with cool water. ",
  "dn2:80.2": "In the same way, a mendicant drenches, steeps, fills, and spreads their body with bliss free of rapture. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with bliss free of rapture. ",
  "dn7:2.5": "When a mendicant knows and sees like this, would it be appropriate to say of them: ",
  "dn7:2.6": "‘The soul and the body are the same thing’ or ‘The soul and the body are different things’?” ",
  "dn7:2.7": "“It would, reverend.” ",
  "dn7:2.8": "",
  "dn7:2.9": "“But reverends, I know and see like this. ",
  "dn7:2.10": "Nevertheless, I do not say: ",
  "dn7:2.11": "‘The soul and the body are the same thing’ or ‘The soul and the body are different things’. … ",

# "dn2:80.3  VIRTUAL-REMAP  3rd combined",

  "dn2:81.0": "4.3.2.8. Fourth Absorption ",

# "ANCHOR-REMAP",
  "dn7:3.3": "fourth absorption. ",
  "dn2:81.1": "Furthermore, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, a mendicant enters and remains in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness. ",

  "dn2:81.2": "They sit spreading their body through with pure bright mind. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with pure bright mind. ",

  "dn2:82.1": "It’s like someone sitting wrapped from head to foot with white cloth. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread over with white cloth. ",
  "dn2:82.2": "In the same way, they sit spreading their body through with pure bright mind. There’s no part of the body that’s not spread with pure bright mind. ",
